Our Story
/$
$

Christian arqueros
/$
$
Christian has been in hospitality for 21 years. His expertise has risen from spending time in all facets of the industry. Christian started his career in Food and beverage by spending 10 years at Universal Orlando City Walk. Where he worked as a bar manager for Latin Quarter. Since then, Christian worked for the Orange County convention center as a catering bartender, opened five-star hotels such as Omni Resort at Champions Gate & Rosen Shingle Creek, and worked with Bar Starz Orlando as a bar specialist. His experience led him to help develop a local restaurant into 16 locations while overseeing all the bar training and bar layout & design for each location. Christian has studied wine throughout his travels over the years in Napa Valley, Mendoza Argentina, Central Valley Chile, and Tuscany, Italy. He currently owns and operates a very popular wine bar in the Mills 50 district of Orlando called Grape & The Grain.
